<p></p>.<p>
<a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/copd_chronic_obstructive_pulmonary_disease/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">COPD</a> is characterized by a longstanding (chronic) obstruction to air flow out of the <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/image-collection/lungs_picture/picture.htm" rel="img" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">lungs</a>. It can take different forms and have different symptoms. Symptoms of COPD can also vary in severity. Symptoms include</p>.<p>
Other possible symptoms can include</p>.<p>
The advanced stages of <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/copd_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">COPD</a> can lead to symptoms like swelling of the <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/feet_facts_quiz/quiz.htm" rel="quiz" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">feet</a> and ankles, bluish discoloration of the skin and mucous membranes (cyanosis), morning <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/headache/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">headaches</a>, and <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/weight_loss/article.htm" rel="sub" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">weight loss</a>.</p>.<p>
The primary cause of <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/copd_chronic_obstructive_pulmonary_disease/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">chronic obstructive pulmonary disease</a> is <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/smoking_and_quitting_smoking/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">cigarette smoking</a> and/or exposure to <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/smoking_and_quitting_smoking/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">cigarette</a> smoke. Other causes include air pollution, infectious diseases, and certain genetic or <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/genetic_disease/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">inherited</a> conditions like <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/alpha_1_antitrypsin_deficiency/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">alpha-1 antitrypsin deficiency</a>. 
